    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've designed:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats`\n\n### What I found\n\nThe codebase has a well-established pattern from `uv cache size` to follow exactly:\n- `uv cache size` is gated behind `PreviewFeature::CacheSize`\n- The 11 `CacheBucket` variants each map to a versioned subdirectory (e.g. `wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`, `git-v0`, etc.)\n- `Cache::bucket(CacheBucket)` returns a `PathBuf` to each bucket's directory\n- `diskus::DiskUsage` is already imported and used for size counting\n- `human_readable_bytes` from `uv_console` is already re-exported in `commands/mod.rs`\n\n### 8 changes across 8 files\n\n1. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheStats = 1 << 21` preview feature variant + string mappings\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + `StatsArgs` struct (mirrors `SizeArgs`)\n3. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm routing `CacheCommand::Stats` → `commands::cache_stats`\n4. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Re-export `cache_stats` function + declare module\n5. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — The handler: iterate all 11 buckets, `DiskUsage` each one, print aligned table with separator + Total row\n6. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` command helper + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter\n7. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — Register `mod cache_stats`\n8. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — Integration tests for empty cache, raw output, `--human` output\n\n### Notable design decision\n`CacheBucket::iter()` omits the `Python` variant, but the stats command lists all 11 variants explicitly (including `Python`) to give complete visibility.",
